Specification for `main.go` — the orchestrator CLI, stage 1 of the pipeline. Reads raw text from stdin and emits a traced compression job to stdout.

# entity CompressionJob {#compression_job}

The job message the orchestrator emits — the input contract of `compression-py`.

## field request_id

UUID v4 string, generated here and only here. Every downstream service copies it verbatim.

## field source_service

Constant string `orchestrator-go`.

## field payload

The raw text to compress: stdin content with leading/trailing whitespace trimmed. Non-empty (see the error below).

# func main {#orchestrator_main}

## flow

1. Read all of stdin and trim surrounding whitespace.
2. If the trimmed payload is empty, emit `PP_EMPTY_INPUT` and stop.
3. Generate the `request_id` (UUID v4 from `crypto/rand`).
4. Log acceptance: request id and payload size in bytes.
5. Marshal the `CompressionJob` {#compression_job} and write it to stdout as a single line.
6. Log emission and exit `0`.

## error PP_EMPTY_INPUT

Raised when stdin is empty or whitespace-only. Emit the shared error envelope with this code, `source_service` set to `orchestrator-go`, an empty `request_id`, and exit `1`.
